                                         CAPE TOWN - Eastern Cape police have impounded two minibus taxis after a route dispute turned violent. It's understood a row broke out in Mthatha on Saturday when the Uncedo Taxi Association interfered in the Border Alliance Taxi Association's operations at the local taxi rank. The police's Mzukisi Fatyela says the dispute resulted in stone-throwing. “One of our members was injured during that stone throwing. The drivers of the taxis ran away at the arrival of the police. And also, we confiscated two combis that were already damaged.” No arrests have yet been made.